**Code Explanation:**

The code defines the architecture and loss functions required for the Super-Resolution Denoising Autoencoder (SR-DAE) and prepares the training loop configuration. 1. Architecture (SR_DAE): A multi-scale U-Net is implemented with an encoder-decoder structure. The skip connections incorporate gated cross-attention via the AttentionBlock, which allows the model to selectively focus on relevant spatial features from the encoder (e.g., CIB-traced star-forming regions) when reconstructing the high-resolution tSZ map. 2. Composite Loss (CompositeLoss): - Focal L1 Loss (FocalL1Loss): Computes a pixel-wise L1 loss that is modulated by a focal term (1 - exp(-|error|))^gamma to down-weight small, easy-to-fit noise and focus on larger structural errors. It also applies a heavy weighting factor (default 10^3) to pixels within the significance mask to prioritize high-intensity baryonic features. - Spectral Consistency Loss (SpectralLoss): A fully differentiable PyTorch implementation of the flat-sky power spectrum estimator (mimicking utils.powers). It computes the 2D FFT, bins the power into 1D multipole (ell) bins, and penalizes the log-scale mean squared error between the predicted and target power spectra. 3. Training Configuration: The configure_training function sets up the AdamW optimizer and a OneCycleLR scheduler. The train_step function encapsulates a single forward-backward pass, integrating mixed-precision training (via torch.cuda.amp) and gradient clipping to ensure training stability given the high dynamic range of the Focal Loss. A dummy forward and backward pass is executed in the __main__ block to verify that the architecture and loss functions are correctly instantiated and differentiable.

