**Code Explanation:**

This script performs the sensitivity and ablation analysis as outlined in Step 7. It consists of three main parts: 1. Ablated Model Training: We define an AblatedDataset that loads only the first 3 channels (the spectral difference maps: 150-90, 217-150, 353-217 GHz) from the pre-processed features, discarding the CIB auxiliary channels. We then train a control SR_DAE model (in_channels=3) using the exact same training and fine-tuning procedures (30 epochs of standard training + 15 epochs of fine-tuning) and random seeds as the full model. 2. Performance Evaluation (r_ell): We evaluate both the full model (loaded from data/finetuned_model.pth) and the ablated model on the test set. We compute the cross-correlation coefficient r_ell between the reconstructed and ground-truth tSZ maps using the utils.powers function, and print the mean r_ell at key multipole bins to quantify the performance gain provided by the CIB features. 3. Cluster Injection and Reconstruction Threshold: We generate synthetic GNFW cluster profiles for a range of masses (log M_500 in [13.5, 15.0]). We select a null patch from the test set (a region with negligible intrinsic tSZ signal) and inject the cluster signal into the observed features by simulating the beam-smoothed spectral differences. We then pass these modified features through the full model and measure the reconstructed peak Compton-y value compared to the injected peak, determining the minimum mass threshold for reliable reconstruction.

